1
00:00:01,253 --> 00:00:02,686
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> Angel:

2
00:00:02,853 --> 00:00:05,321
CORDELIA: <i>The rain of fire,</i>
<i>even blotting out the sun...</i>

3
00:00:05,493 --> 00:00:07,529
<i>... those were the first steps</i>
<i>to something bigger.</i>

4
00:00:07,693 --> 00:00:09,012
We need Angelus.

5
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:10,922
CORDELIA:
Angelus.

6
00:00:11,093 --> 00:00:15,769
There's something bigger, something
worse. The Beast has a boss.

7
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,161
FRED:
<i>Angelus has escaped.</i>

8
00:00:18,373 --> 00:00:20,011
- He's gonna kill us.
- I know.

9
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,969
Why do you think I let him out?

10
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,886
We're gonna save Angel.
I know who we need to help us do it.

11
00:00:27,053 --> 00:00:29,442
This is Faith, the vampire slayer.

12
00:00:29,613 --> 00:00:32,810
If Angelus needs putting down,
I'll be the one to do it, not you.

13
00:00:32,973 --> 00:00:34,452
What is this, Angelus?

14
00:00:34,613 --> 00:00:36,843
She's here to seriously mess up
your boss's plans.

15
00:00:38,693 --> 00:00:42,652
You are weak. You're nothing.
You could not even defeat me.

16
00:00:42,813 --> 00:00:43,882
Ain't that the truth?

17
00:00:45,653 --> 00:00:46,847
[ROARS]

18
00:00:49,973 --> 00:00:52,885
You mean killing the Beast
really does bring back the sun?

19
00:00:53,093 --> 00:00:54,492
[GRUNTS]

20
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:57,247
Swing and a miss, slugger.
Sorry about...

21
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:04,004
I guess we'll have to take a rain check
on that whole "eviscerating you" thing.

22
00:01:04,693 --> 00:01:07,332
- I don't know how...
- What?

23
00:01:08,413 --> 00:01:10,290
CORDELIA:
We're having a baby.

24
00:01:15,613 --> 00:01:17,126
WESLEY:
Sit here.

25
00:01:40,493 --> 00:01:42,324
Hold this.

26
00:01:48,253 --> 00:01:50,403
I'll get bandages.

27
00:01:50,853 --> 00:01:52,332
No drama. I'm good.

28
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:56,885
You were nearly killed.

29
00:01:57,853 --> 00:01:59,969
Could use a shower.

30
00:02:00,973 --> 00:02:03,123
Of course.

31
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:10,052
Faith, are you sure you're okay?

32
00:02:12,653 --> 00:02:14,245
Little sticky.

33
00:03:29,373 --> 00:03:31,489
[SCREAMING]

34
00:03:34,053 --> 00:03:36,044
[GASPING]

35
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:01,564
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

36
00:04:07,853 --> 00:04:09,844
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

37
00:04:11,373 --> 00:04:13,329
Compliments of the lady.

38
00:04:16,373 --> 00:04:19,922
Yeah, as if. I couldn't believe
how easy it was luring the slayer...

39
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,924
...to my welcome-home-
from-prison party.

40
00:04:22,093 --> 00:04:24,653
Wish I could've been there
when she saw the Beast.

41
00:04:24,813 --> 00:04:28,442
Guy wasn't gonna win any personality
contest, but he put on a good show.

42
00:04:28,613 --> 00:04:30,683
He slapped her around real nice.

43
00:04:30,973 --> 00:04:32,452
Like a little bunny?

44
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:36,088
A bloody, whimpering bunny.

45
00:04:37,453 --> 00:04:41,002
When she was tenderized,
I gave Rocko the shaft.

46
00:04:41,173 --> 00:04:43,562
Never saw it coming. Dumb-ass.

47
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:47,567
Yeah, soul boy, nice job
bringing the sun back.

48
00:04:54,973 --> 00:04:58,648
Oh, hey, Angelus.
Buy you a warm one?

49
00:04:58,813 --> 00:04:59,882
Maybe after.

50
00:05:00,413 --> 00:05:01,482
After what?

51
00:05:01,653 --> 00:05:05,885
After I rip out your windpipe so it stops
making that annoying talky sound.

52
00:05:06,053 --> 00:05:08,521
Wait! I have a condition.

53
00:05:08,693 --> 00:05:11,605
Go, boy! Dirty bitch! Tourette's.
You've heard of it, right?

54
00:05:11,773 --> 00:05:15,209
Yeah. Causes uncontrollable impulses,
like yanking out throats.

55
00:05:15,413 --> 00:05:17,563
[CHOKING]

56
00:05:17,853 --> 00:05:20,651
MAN:
<i>Hello, Angelus.</i>

57
00:05:20,813 --> 00:05:24,010
<i>It's time we had that talk.</i>

58
00:05:30,293 --> 00:05:32,682
Release

59
00:06:16,533 --> 00:06:18,524
- Where are you?
- Wherever you want me to be.

60
00:06:18,693 --> 00:06:21,730
<i>I'm where it's warm and soft.</i>

61
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:25,124
[GAGGING]

62
00:06:26,213 --> 00:06:28,408
Hide and seek, huh?
Okay, I'll play.

63
00:06:28,573 --> 00:06:34,011
<i>Playtime's over. You've been a bad boy.</i>
<i>Killed my favorite pet.</i>

64
00:06:34,173 --> 00:06:37,529
Yeah, well, thought that might
get your attention.

65
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:47,561
<i>Initiative. I like that,</i>
<i>but you needn 't have bothered.</i>

66
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:49,928
<i>I've had my eyes on you</i>
<i>for some time.</i>

67
00:06:50,093 --> 00:06:52,402
Hey, baby, how about a hit?

68
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:56,450
- You like to watch, huh?
- <i>One of the things we have in common.</i>

69
00:06:56,613 --> 00:07:00,049
I don't know about that.
I'm more of a hands-on kind of a guy.

70
00:07:00,213 --> 00:07:02,204
You, scram!

71
00:07:02,373 --> 00:07:03,726
Hey, man.

72
00:07:05,213 --> 00:07:07,124
Okay, come on. You got a pair...

73
00:07:07,293 --> 00:07:10,365
...or the wind you're blowing up
my tailpipe is all you can muster?

74
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,808
Hey, here's a kooky idea.

75
00:07:12,973 --> 00:07:16,090
Now that I've killed your little pet rock,
how about a face-to-face?

76
00:07:16,253 --> 00:07:18,084
- Assuming that you've got one.
- <i>Don 't...</i>

77
00:07:18,253 --> 00:07:20,926
- worry. We'll meet when you're...

78
00:07:21,093 --> 00:07:22,082
<i>- ready.</i>

79
00:07:22,253 --> 00:07:23,891
Oh, come on. Why the stall, huh?

80
00:07:24,053 --> 00:07:27,409
You whipped up a rain of fire,
blotted out the sun, earthquakes...

81
00:07:27,573 --> 00:07:31,566
...all to maneuver the Brady Bunch
into releasing Angel's inner me, huh?

82
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:34,406
- Don't you want to kick the tires?
- <i>So beautifully...</i>

83
00:07:34,573 --> 00:07:38,407
- vain. But the whirlwind
doesn't always revolve around you.

84
00:07:38,573 --> 00:07:40,928
Destruction sometimes is its own...

85
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:42,082
<i>- reward.</i>

86
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:44,767
Hey, you're preaching to the guy
who ate the choir.

87
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:50,644
But wait. It was you,
wasn't it, huh?

88
00:07:50,813 --> 00:07:54,931
You pulled just the wrong strings
to make them think it was their idea.

89
00:07:55,093 --> 00:07:58,768
Got them to yank that white,
fluffy soul, and stuff it in a jar...

90
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:01,401
...and then gone, baby, gone.
- <i>Couldn 't risk them...</i>

91
00:08:01,573 --> 00:08:03,564
- putting it back in you.

92
00:08:04,093 --> 00:08:06,084
I have wonderful plans for you, my...

93
00:08:06,253 --> 00:08:07,811
<i>- sweet boy.</i>

94
00:08:07,973 --> 00:08:11,761
Yeah. The thing is, as far
as plans go, I make my own.

95
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:14,731
So, you know, thanks
for stopping by my head.

96
00:08:14,893 --> 00:08:17,805
<i>You would dare to defy me?</i>

97
00:08:17,973 --> 00:08:22,205
Defy who? A big, scary voice?
Hey, I got one of those too.

98
00:08:22,373 --> 00:08:26,412
You want to hear it?
You can kiss my vampire ass!

99
00:08:26,573 --> 00:08:28,165
That do anything for you?

100
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:29,607
[KNOCKING]

101
00:08:29,813 --> 00:08:32,930
CONNOR:
Hey, brought you another blanket.

102
00:08:37,093 --> 00:08:38,845
You've gotta keep warm.

103
00:08:39,053 --> 00:08:40,372
[SIGHS]

104
00:08:44,413 --> 00:08:48,292
- You okay?
- Just a little woozy.

105
00:08:48,533 --> 00:08:53,049
Could be the whole "Angelus nailing me
with the crossbow" thingy.

106
00:08:58,773 --> 00:09:02,209
Or it could be the baby.

107
00:09:02,853 --> 00:09:03,842
His way of saying...

108
00:09:04,013 --> 00:09:05,731
Hello?

109
00:09:06,173 --> 00:09:09,404
Hey, I got places to go,
friends to kill.

110
00:09:09,573 --> 00:09:12,451
Well, not actually my friends,
but you get the idea.

111
00:09:13,373 --> 00:09:17,127
You got any more bluster
you want to blow up there?

112
00:09:18,093 --> 00:09:20,129
That's what I thought.

113
00:09:21,253 --> 00:09:26,930
Dude, whatever you're on,
I'll give you the girl for a gram.

114
00:09:30,213 --> 00:09:32,568
You're sure Faith's all right?

115
00:09:32,973 --> 00:09:34,167
Yeah.

116
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:39,327
When Wesley called, he said that
she was hurt bad, but she's a slayer.

117
00:09:39,493 --> 00:09:42,291
- They're really strong, right?
- For a human.

118
00:09:42,653 --> 00:09:45,690
God, I can't believe
Angelus killed the Beast.

119
00:09:45,853 --> 00:09:47,764
He fought dirty.

120
00:09:48,213 --> 00:09:53,446
Maybe this means we did the right
thing, bringing Angelus back.

121
00:09:53,613 --> 00:09:57,322
Right. He's a real hero.

122
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:03,451
Connor...

123
00:10:04,013 --> 00:10:09,292
...Angelus cannot fight his true nature.
It's who he is.

124
00:10:09,693 --> 00:10:13,572
But by killing the Beast,
he's made the world a little safer...

125
00:10:14,573 --> 00:10:16,165
...for our family.

126
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:19,166
You didn't have that
the first time around.

127
00:10:19,373 --> 00:10:23,764
- But now you will.
- I won't ever let anything hurt you.

128
00:10:25,493 --> 00:10:27,085
Either of you.

129
00:10:27,493 --> 00:10:28,846
I know you won't.

130
00:10:29,973 --> 00:10:34,012
But just remember, this is ours.

131
00:10:34,373 --> 00:10:37,171
Nobody else needs to know
how lucky we are.

132
00:10:39,293 --> 00:10:41,409
- Are you ashamed of me?
- What?

133
00:10:43,653 --> 00:10:46,247
- No.
- Then why don't you want to tell them?

134
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:48,722
Because they wouldn't understand.

135
00:10:48,893 --> 00:10:53,250
Our baby is growing so fast,
it would scare them.

136
00:10:54,813 --> 00:10:58,089
And that fear might make them
want to kill it...

137
00:10:58,413 --> 00:11:00,324
...like they wanted to kill you.

138
00:11:02,213 --> 00:11:04,522
But trust me, Connor...

139
00:11:05,213 --> 00:11:07,488
...it won't be too long.

140
00:11:08,213 --> 00:11:11,728
They're all going to know
what's growing inside of me.

141
00:11:16,613 --> 00:11:18,046
Meet your new best friend.

142
00:11:18,213 --> 00:11:21,091
If he shows up, the sanctuary spell
should keep us safe, but...

143
00:11:21,253 --> 00:11:22,845
But? There's always a but.

144
00:11:23,013 --> 00:11:25,447
When this is over, can we have
a big "but" moratorium?

145
00:11:25,613 --> 00:11:28,252
Did I mention the only shots
I'm good at involve tequila?

146
00:11:28,613 --> 00:11:31,491
Do you think Angelus is planning
a repeat performance?

147
00:11:31,653 --> 00:11:35,009
- He's gotta know we'd be prepared.
- Doesn't mean we drop our guard.

148
00:11:35,173 --> 00:11:37,562
If he pops a fang in here,
thwack him where it hurts.

149
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:39,530
Good night, not-so-sweet prince.

150
00:11:39,693 --> 00:11:42,810
I'll re-check downstairs. Make sure
he can't creep into any tunnels.

151
00:11:42,973 --> 00:11:45,043
Yeah, if Lilah managed
to break and enter...

152
00:11:48,413 --> 00:11:50,802
Thought you were more of a taser girl.

153
00:11:52,813 --> 00:11:54,212
Sorry. I've...

154
00:11:55,693 --> 00:11:57,604
How's Cordy?

155
00:11:58,013 --> 00:12:01,130
You know. Tired, I guess.

156
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:05,687
- Maybe I should stop up and check...
- No! She doesn't wanna see anyone yet.

157
00:12:05,853 --> 00:12:08,367
She just wanted some...

158
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:09,842
...soup.

159
00:12:11,493 --> 00:12:13,051
Really hot soup.

160
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:18,370
Odd bird. And getting birdier.

161
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:21,411
You don't think
he and Cordy are still...?

162
00:12:21,573 --> 00:12:24,610
Could be the love bug, but I'm
not picking up warm fuzzies.

163
00:12:24,773 --> 00:12:26,764
I just can't get a good read on it.

164
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:28,969
Not much of the warm
or the fuzzies going on.

165
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:30,532
Why should they be different?

166
00:12:30,693 --> 00:12:34,003
He's probably just upset
about Faith benching him.

167
00:12:34,173 --> 00:12:37,449
Anybody else think maybe
that was a humongous mistake?

168
00:12:37,613 --> 00:12:40,571
Not unless we want Angel back
in anything other than a dustpan.

169
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:44,885
Connor's better off playing nursemaid,
or whatever he's doing with Cordy.

170
00:12:45,053 --> 00:12:47,647
Yeah, but Wes said Faith
kind of got demolished.

171
00:12:47,813 --> 00:12:51,044
She's supposed to be our best chance
of getting Angel back.

172
00:12:51,613 --> 00:12:54,081
But what if she's not up to it?

173
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:01,572
Squeaky clean. Let's blow.

174
00:13:05,373 --> 00:13:07,807
Right. Sorry about your bathroom.

175
00:13:08,533 --> 00:13:10,888
- Let's do it.
- I'm not worried about the bathroom.

176
00:13:11,453 --> 00:13:14,445
Although I'm fairly sure my
security deposit's a complete loss.

177
00:13:16,573 --> 00:13:19,041
I need to know you're
in the game, Faith.

178
00:13:19,213 --> 00:13:20,532
All the way.

179
00:13:24,893 --> 00:13:26,167
[SIGHS]

180
00:13:26,373 --> 00:13:28,603
Five-by-five, boss.

181
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:41,806
If I were a runic transcription guide,
I would be...

182
00:13:42,093 --> 00:13:44,971
...shelved wrong.
ANGEL: Talking to yourself, Fred?

183
00:13:45,693 --> 00:13:47,285
A lot of that going around.

184
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:51,168
You can't hurt me.
We did a no-demon-violence thingy.

185
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:54,405
Oh, the sanctuary spell. Shucks.

186
00:13:54,573 --> 00:13:56,962
Oh, wait a minute, I think I...

187
00:13:59,453 --> 00:14:04,481
Oh, yeah. Kind of thought you pesky
Pls would be humming that old tune...

188
00:14:04,653 --> 00:14:06,723
...so I picked up a little something.

189
00:14:06,893 --> 00:14:08,884
Lets me be as demon-y
as I want to be.

190
00:14:09,053 --> 00:14:10,281
FRED:
I don't believe you.

191
00:14:12,853 --> 00:14:14,571
How about now?

192
00:14:15,173 --> 00:14:16,572
What do you want?

193
00:14:16,733 --> 00:14:19,201
Maybe I just miss you.

194
00:14:19,613 --> 00:14:24,323
Well, since you brought it up,
let's talk Beastmaster.

195
00:14:24,493 --> 00:14:26,882
- What do you got?
- Nothing.

196
00:14:27,053 --> 00:14:29,089
Come on, Fred.

197
00:14:30,093 --> 00:14:34,371
All this raw material,
brainiac like you...

198
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:39,049
...you must have a theory.
- Lf I did, you're the last person I'd tell.

199
00:14:41,653 --> 00:14:45,248
Well, all right, then. I'll just
have to figure it out myself, huh?

200
00:14:45,413 --> 00:14:48,962
Let's see, take these...

201
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,608
...and this.
Thanks for nothing.

202
00:14:52,293 --> 00:14:55,888
I do know one thing.
You're out of your league.

203
00:14:56,533 --> 00:15:00,162
What you're up against, he'll make
you his bitch, just like the Beast.

204
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:03,211
So if you're going to kill me,
just get it over with.

205
00:15:04,213 --> 00:15:05,726
"Made in China"?

206
00:15:17,893 --> 00:15:19,611
Lorne!

207
00:15:23,253 --> 00:15:24,527
Can't beat a good book.

208
00:15:24,693 --> 00:15:26,012
[GUN CLICKS]

209
00:15:27,453 --> 00:15:29,330
Too bad. I was
just starting to have fun.

210
00:15:29,493 --> 00:15:30,687
CONNOR:
Why stop now?

211
00:15:37,813 --> 00:15:39,246
Connor!

212
00:15:41,293 --> 00:15:44,729
Well, isn't that interesting.

213
00:15:53,293 --> 00:15:54,362
Nice try, Fred.

214
00:15:55,373 --> 00:15:59,844
Think how close you came to stopping
me when I'm slaughtering your friends.

215
00:16:00,013 --> 00:16:01,765
Toodles.

216
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:09,006
- We track him, we find him, we...
- Get your asses kicked?

217
00:16:09,173 --> 00:16:11,050
I don't know, wild guess.

218
00:16:19,293 --> 00:16:22,365
Sucky spell, huh? You think
it would at least go to the sidewalk.

219
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,489
Let him go.
This is between you and me.

220
00:16:24,653 --> 00:16:28,965
It's never just between you and me,
Faith. Wes will always be in the middle.

221
00:16:29,173 --> 00:16:33,485
That's it, do the math. Can you
get to me before I snap his neck?

222
00:16:33,653 --> 00:16:37,168
You still that fast?
Wes is just dying to find out.

223
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:38,812
- Aren't you, Wes?
- Do it!

224
00:16:38,973 --> 00:16:43,489
That's it, come on. Do it.
Take your shot and save the world.

225
00:16:43,653 --> 00:16:45,484
Come on, what are you waiting for?

226
00:16:47,493 --> 00:16:50,690
All about choices, Faith. The ones
we make and the ones we don't.

227
00:16:50,853 --> 00:16:53,731
Oh, and the consequences.
Those are always fun.

228
00:16:54,053 --> 00:16:57,932
Don't worry about good old Wes.
What's one more dead body to us?

229
00:16:58,093 --> 00:16:59,765
Come on.

230
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:01,207
Where's my girl?

231
00:17:02,013 --> 00:17:03,002
GUNN:
Faith!

232
00:17:14,813 --> 00:17:16,132
[COUGHING]

233
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,766
Go!

234
00:17:19,053 --> 00:17:20,611
He's gone.

235
00:17:27,933 --> 00:17:30,208
Cordy! Cordy?

236
00:17:32,253 --> 00:17:34,244
[TOILET FLUSHING]

237
00:17:34,693 --> 00:17:35,762
CORDELIA:
What?

238
00:17:36,893 --> 00:17:39,123
- Are you okay?
- Sure.

239
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:44,290
Except for the morning sickness
that can't tell time.

240
