306
00:21:58,893 --> 00:22:01,965
One, because I'm evil,
so the friends thing, that's out.

307
00:22:02,133 --> 00:22:05,603
And two, if I had any friends,
they wouldn't be living inside my head.

308
00:22:05,773 --> 00:22:09,732
<i>Like you're forced to live inside Angel's?</i>

309
00:22:09,893 --> 00:22:11,565
[LAUGHING]

310
00:22:11,773 --> 00:22:14,082
<i>Because you're the voice</i>
<i>in there, aren 't you?</i>

311
00:22:14,253 --> 00:22:18,326
<i>Just beneath the surface,</i>
<i>buried under all that goodness.</i>

312
00:22:18,493 --> 00:22:24,966
<i>Fully conscious, fully aware, but trapped,</i>
<i>unable to move or speak.</i>

313
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:27,522
<i>Powerless to act on your desires.</i>

314
00:22:27,693 --> 00:22:33,563
<i>So thirsty, so helpless.</i>
<i>It must be agony.</i>

315
00:22:34,293 --> 00:22:36,011
I'm getting real bored
with this game.

316
00:22:36,173 --> 00:22:38,812
<i>Then how about a round</i>
<i>of show and tell?</i>

317
00:22:38,973 --> 00:22:42,090
<i>Soul, soul, who has your soul?</i>

318
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:46,486
<i>Oh, right. Me.</i>

319
00:22:48,573 --> 00:22:50,086
More smoke and mirrors.

320
00:22:50,253 --> 00:22:52,164
<i>Only a glamour, yes.</i>

321
00:22:52,773 --> 00:22:56,049
<i>But I assure you, my sweet,</i>
<i>this very moment...</i>

322
00:22:56,213 --> 00:23:00,764
<i>... I hold the real thing in the palms</i>
<i>of my very corporeal hands...</i>

323
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:05,085
<i>... and I will restore it</i>
<i>if you don 't behave.</i>

324
00:23:05,253 --> 00:23:10,168
<i>I'll put you back in your box, Angelus,</i>
<i>and bury you so far inside Angel...</i>

325
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:14,087
<i>... you'll never claw</i>
<i>your way out again.</i>

326
00:23:19,653 --> 00:23:24,283
All right, what do you
want me to do...

327
00:23:25,693 --> 00:23:27,649
...master?

328
00:23:37,853 --> 00:23:41,766
- You really think he'll come back?
- Measure twice, cut once.

329
00:23:43,373 --> 00:23:45,045
Yeah.

330
00:23:45,373 --> 00:23:49,127
- Since this worked so well the first time.
- Not your fault.

331
00:23:49,293 --> 00:23:52,285
- I should have had him.
- Fred, you got out of it alive, so...

332
00:23:52,453 --> 00:23:55,092
Because he let me.

333
00:23:56,853 --> 00:23:58,411
Why not?

334
00:23:58,573 --> 00:24:01,041
All the little mouse could do
was squeak at him.

335
00:24:01,213 --> 00:24:03,966
Then next time Minnie will take
a chunk out of his cheese.

336
00:24:04,133 --> 00:24:07,682
If you really think you did something
wrong, don't do it again. That simple.

337
00:24:09,253 --> 00:24:10,845
Is it?

338
00:24:14,933 --> 00:24:16,491
Sometimes.

339
00:24:16,653 --> 00:24:17,927
Don't.

340
00:24:19,653 --> 00:24:22,167
- All we ever do is turn away.
- Fred, l...

341
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:26,849
I know. Whatever Wes was feeling,
whatever he thought might...

342
00:24:27,013 --> 00:24:30,449
I should have told him it was never
gonna happen. Think I don't know that?

343
00:24:30,613 --> 00:24:33,525
- That's not what I was gonna say.
- But it's what you think.

344
00:24:35,573 --> 00:24:36,892
Isn't it?

345
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:43,961
I'm sorry.

346
00:24:44,773 --> 00:24:46,923
It's not about that anymore.
You know that.

347
00:24:47,293 --> 00:24:49,488
All I know...

348
00:24:50,773 --> 00:24:52,365
...is, I miss you.

349
00:24:56,213 --> 00:24:58,602
Can't we just go back...

350
00:24:59,613 --> 00:25:01,729
...before any of this?

351
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:06,369
I just want to go back, Charles.

352
00:25:12,573 --> 00:25:14,564
I just want to...

353
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:31,051
I...

354
