416
00:30:07,533 --> 00:30:10,366
Hey, you're pretty.
You want to make out?

417
00:30:13,533 --> 00:30:16,605
There was a vampire in here earlier.
Tall, dark hair... Listen!

418
00:30:16,773 --> 00:30:20,686
- Okay. God, what's your issue?
- Tall, dark hair, talking to himself.

419
00:30:20,853 --> 00:30:22,332
- Let go.
- Did you see him?

420
00:30:22,493 --> 00:30:24,723
No, I didn't! Stop it!
You're hurting me!

421
00:30:28,693 --> 00:30:31,048
She doesn't know anything.

422
00:30:38,373 --> 00:30:39,362
WESLEY:
Maybe not.

423
00:30:39,773 --> 00:30:41,604
- What are you doing?
- Shut up!

424
00:30:41,933 --> 00:30:44,845
The tracks on your arms.
You've been here two days straight?

425
00:30:45,013 --> 00:30:46,492
- Answer me!
- Yeah.

426
00:30:46,653 --> 00:30:49,770
Stop. Yes, four. Four days.

427
00:30:49,933 --> 00:30:52,401
Then you must have seen
the vampire we're looking for.

428
00:30:52,573 --> 00:30:55,371
Angelus, I saw him.
He... He... Please.

429
00:30:55,533 --> 00:30:57,728
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

430
00:30:57,933 --> 00:31:00,049
Oh, I don't know!
Please, stop!

431
00:31:00,213 --> 00:31:02,329
He was talking to himself.
What was he saying?

432
00:31:02,493 --> 00:31:06,327
I don't know. It was like
he was talking to someone else.

433
00:31:06,493 --> 00:31:09,929
It was all "a rain of fire"
and "pulling strings" and "a soul."

434
00:31:10,093 --> 00:31:11,606
That's all I heard.

435
00:31:11,893 --> 00:31:14,248
Please stop. It hurts.

436
00:31:14,493 --> 00:31:15,812
[SCREAMS]

437
00:31:17,573 --> 00:31:20,041
Have you totally lost it?

438
00:31:20,213 --> 00:31:23,171
I avoided the main arteries.
She'll live.

439
00:31:23,333 --> 00:31:25,289
If that's what you call this.

440
00:31:26,293 --> 00:31:31,811
Whatever's controlling the Beast,
it's made contact with Angelus.

441
00:31:33,853 --> 00:31:36,321
So what? Torturing humans
part of the new makeover?

442
00:31:36,493 --> 00:31:38,688
- Did what I had to because you couldn't.
- I hit her.

443
00:31:38,853 --> 00:31:41,526
- You think that's new to her?
- You crossed it back there.

444
00:31:41,693 --> 00:31:44,002
You have a problem
with a little torture now?

445
00:31:44,173 --> 00:31:46,368
I recall a time
when you rather enjoyed it.

446
00:31:47,013 --> 00:31:49,481
Yeah, well, it's not me anymore.
You know that.

447
00:31:49,813 --> 00:31:52,930
Nice to have this along, though.
Just in case.

448
00:31:54,933 --> 00:31:57,731
I remember what you did to me.

449
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:01,803
The broken glass, the shallow cuts...

450
00:32:02,133 --> 00:32:04,772
...so I would remain conscious.

451
00:32:06,173 --> 00:32:07,845
You think I'd hurt you again?

452
00:32:08,013 --> 00:32:11,562
This the part where you tell me
you've turned a new leaf? Found God?

453
00:32:11,733 --> 00:32:13,291
Inner peace?

454
00:32:13,453 --> 00:32:16,365
We both know that isn't true.
You haven't changed. You can't.

455
00:32:16,533 --> 00:32:18,205
- Wes...
- Because you're sick.

456
00:32:18,373 --> 00:32:19,647
You've always been sick.

457
00:32:19,813 --> 00:32:22,202
It goes right down to the roots,
rotting your soul.

458
00:32:22,373 --> 00:32:25,809
That's why your friends turned on you,
why the Council tried to kill you.

459
00:32:25,973 --> 00:32:29,363
No one trusts you. You're a rabid dog
who should have been put down...

460
00:32:29,533 --> 00:32:31,330
[GRUNTS]

461
00:32:31,573 --> 00:32:34,007
See? Wasn't so hard, was it?

462
00:32:36,853 --> 00:32:39,128
It's what you'll need to beat him.

463
00:32:41,373 --> 00:32:43,011
No.

464
00:32:45,133 --> 00:32:47,693
You have to be willing
to take it all the way.

465
00:32:51,653 --> 00:32:56,488
I can't risk killing Angel.
Not after what he's done for me.

466
00:32:59,453 --> 00:33:02,206
There's gotta be another way.

467
00:33:03,893 --> 00:33:10,366
Oh. Smacked in the noggin with
a two-by-four wrapped in velvet.

468
00:33:10,653 --> 00:33:12,803
Yeah, that's what it felt like.

469
00:33:12,973 --> 00:33:15,567
I am so, so beyond sorry.

470
00:33:15,733 --> 00:33:19,692
Oh, go on. It's the first good nap
I've had since the Apocalypse started.

471
00:33:19,853 --> 00:33:23,129
- So, what did I miss?
- Angelus and his usual freak show.

472
00:33:23,293 --> 00:33:27,127
Everybody still has their necks attached.
The sanctuary spell did its thing?

473
00:33:27,493 --> 00:33:30,769
- Yeah, it's working.
LORNE: Hey, one for the good guys.

474
00:33:30,933 --> 00:33:32,730
And take two away.

475
00:33:32,893 --> 00:33:34,690
I let Angelus walk with Lilah's book...

476
00:33:34,853 --> 00:33:37,492
...and everything Wolfram and Hart
suckered out of you.

477
00:33:37,653 --> 00:33:39,006
I was gonna frame those.

478
00:33:39,173 --> 00:33:42,324
The vampire Moriarty strolls in
waving the anti-mojo mojo...

479
00:33:42,493 --> 00:33:44,529
...anybody would've done the same.
- Mojo?

480
00:33:44,693 --> 00:33:49,403
No-jo. He waved this piece of junk in
my face, and I went all spinal-paralysis.

481
00:33:50,613 --> 00:33:52,365
Put the blame stick down.

482
00:33:52,533 --> 00:33:55,889
Maury's been peddling these to tourists
since L.A. Had cable cars.

483
00:33:56,053 --> 00:33:59,011
Fools the Bermuda shorts off them
every single time.

484
00:33:59,173 --> 00:34:01,289
- Maury?
- You know where this guy is?

485
00:34:01,453 --> 00:34:04,286
Yeah, sure. He hangs his horns
in a shop down on Olive.

486
00:34:04,453 --> 00:34:06,171
- Why?
- Call Wes. Now.

487
00:34:36,933 --> 00:34:38,924
Even if he got the fake hoodoo
from Maury...

488
00:34:39,093 --> 00:34:41,448
...why would Angelus hang around?
- He wouldn't.

489
00:34:41,613 --> 00:34:45,208
But this Maury that Lorne knows
may be able to help us find...

490
00:34:45,373 --> 00:34:47,728
...where Angelus is hiding.

491
00:34:57,453 --> 00:34:59,250
ANGEL:
No.

492
00:34:59,533 --> 00:35:01,364
But I can.

493
00:35:09,013 --> 00:35:12,642
Little birdie in my head told me
you'd be here.

494
00:35:13,893 --> 00:35:16,487
Whoo! Exciting.

495
00:35:24,533 --> 00:35:26,125
Gotta do better than that, Wes.

496
00:35:28,013 --> 00:35:29,651
Come on, I'll give you one more.

497
00:35:33,933 --> 00:35:35,252
Strike three!

498
00:35:40,373 --> 00:35:41,692
Uh-oh.

499
00:35:42,573 --> 00:35:43,972
Vampire with a gun.

500
00:35:45,973 --> 00:35:47,691
I see why he likes this thing.

501
00:35:56,253 --> 00:35:57,572
Wow.

502
00:35:59,173 --> 00:36:02,324
You really have gone soft now,
haven't you?

503
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:04,324
Hey!

504
00:36:04,613 --> 00:36:08,049
You remember that time you tried
to get Angel to kill you...

505
00:36:08,213 --> 00:36:13,731
...because you felt all weepy
over being such a bad little girl?

506
00:36:14,773 --> 00:36:17,128
Do you still feel that way?

507
00:36:17,493 --> 00:36:19,688
Do you still want to die?

508
00:36:21,133 --> 00:36:22,725
- No.
- What's that?

509
00:36:22,893 --> 00:36:24,121
- No.
- I can't hear you.

510
00:36:24,293 --> 00:36:25,851
No!

511
00:36:26,653 --> 00:36:27,972
[GUN COCKING]

512
00:36:29,813 --> 00:36:32,805
Too bad, because you're gonna.

513
00:36:38,533 --> 00:36:39,807
But not like this.

514
00:36:45,613 --> 00:36:47,569
Looks like we got a live one.

515
00:36:49,893 --> 00:36:51,246
For now.

516
00:36:55,853 --> 00:36:58,845
A little tired, sweetie?
Want to take a break?

517
00:37:06,693 --> 00:37:11,050
Now, this is disappointing.
You never used to bleed so easy.

518
00:37:11,213 --> 00:37:14,285
- Screw you!
- Maybe after.

519
00:37:14,773 --> 00:37:18,129
I like my girls to lie still.

520
00:37:20,613 --> 00:37:23,332
Hey, buddy, how's it going in there?

521
00:37:27,213 --> 00:37:31,889
Good old Wes. Always count on him to
tackle a bad situation and make it worse.

522
00:37:32,453 --> 00:37:35,684
I mean, hey, look how you turned out.

523
00:37:37,093 --> 00:37:41,086
But then again, I guess he really
didn't have much to work with, now.

524
00:37:41,333 --> 00:37:43,289
[LAUGHS]

525
00:37:43,493 --> 00:37:45,449
Save the head trip, GQ.

526
00:37:45,613 --> 00:37:48,173
Wes told me you'd try
to get under my skin.

527
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:50,722
Gave me just what I need
to scratch you out.

528
00:37:50,893 --> 00:37:55,569
Oh, don't tell me. The rousing,
stiff-upper-lip speech.

529
00:37:55,733 --> 00:37:58,691
Rah, rah! Good over evil!
Do what must be done!

530
00:37:58,853 --> 00:38:01,367
Hang in there, kitten,
it's almost Friday!

531
00:38:01,533 --> 00:38:04,445
Is that what the scraggly,
little ponce armed you with...

532
00:38:04,613 --> 00:38:08,288
...to fight the big, bad bogeyman?

533
00:38:08,453 --> 00:38:10,762
Yeah. And this.

534
00:38:37,533 --> 00:38:39,649
ANGEL:
That hurt, baby.

535
00:38:39,813 --> 00:38:41,849
I kind of liked it.

536
00:38:42,013 --> 00:38:43,969
[LAUGHING]

537
00:38:45,293 --> 00:38:48,524
How about you? There's my girl.

538
00:38:48,693 --> 00:38:52,163
Knew she was in there somewhere,
dying to come out and play again.

539
00:38:52,333 --> 00:38:54,324
- Shut up.
- I know how it feels.

540
00:38:54,493 --> 00:38:58,486
Forced to be someone you're not.
Hurts to the bone.

541
00:38:58,733 --> 00:39:03,966
You try to bury the pain, but you can't
get the hole deep enough, can you?

542
00:39:04,813 --> 00:39:08,283
No matter how much you dig,
it's still there.

543
00:39:12,533 --> 00:39:18,085
Broken shards stabbing every time
you breathe, cutting you up inside.

544
00:39:18,253 --> 00:39:22,166
You know, there's only one way
to make the pain stop.

545
00:39:23,013 --> 00:39:24,446
Hurt someone else.

546
00:39:57,333 --> 00:39:59,893
Come on, Faith,
you're not even trying.

547
00:40:03,373 --> 00:40:05,284
Or is that why you really
came back, huh?

548
00:40:05,453 --> 00:40:09,002
Not enough to punish yourself
in prison? Is that it?

549
00:40:09,173 --> 00:40:11,482
Looking for someone
to beat the bad out of you?

550
00:40:13,693 --> 00:40:16,924
I could beat you to death,
but it wouldn't make a difference.

551
00:40:17,093 --> 00:40:20,051
Nothing will ever change
who you are, Faith.

552
00:40:20,693 --> 00:40:24,129
You're a murderer, an animal...

553
00:40:25,093 --> 00:40:26,082
...and you enjoy it.

554
00:40:27,613 --> 00:40:28,966
Just like me!

555
00:40:51,973 --> 00:40:53,201
No!

556
00:40:59,733 --> 00:41:03,328
You're wrong. I'm different now.
I'm not like you.

557
00:41:07,573 --> 00:41:09,211
But you will be.

558
00:41:11,653 --> 00:41:12,972
[CRIES]

559
